Ah! The buttons are there but invisible because they have the btn-outline class which makes them transparent/white on a white background! Let me fix that CSS so the buttons are visible.

The Problem:

The buttons have btn-outline class which originally had:

· background: transparent
· border: 2px solid #ffffff (white border)
· color: #ffffff (white text)

On a white background, they disappear!

Fix - Update the Button Classes:

Replace the button HTML in your Species Database tab (around line 785-792) with this:

```html
<!-- EXPAND/COLLAPSE ALL BUTTONS - NOW VISIBLE -->
<div style="display: flex; justify-content: flex-end; margin: 0.5rem 0 1rem 0;">
    <button id="expandAllBtn" class="btn btn-primary" onclick="expandAllSpeciesCards()">
        <i class="fas fa-expand-alt"></i> Expand All
    </button>
    <button id="collapseAllBtn" class="btn btn-primary" onclick="collapseAllSpeciesCards()" style="margin-left: 0.5rem;">
        <i class="fas fa-compress-alt"></i> Collapse All
    </button>
</div>
```

Or, If You Prefer to Keep btn-outline but Make Them Visible:

Add this CSS to your <style> section:

```css
/* Make outline buttons visible on light backgrounds */
.btn-outline {
    background: white;
    border: 2px solid var(--primary);
    color: var(--primary-dark);
}

.btn-outline:hover {
    background: var(--primary);
    color: white;
    border-color: var(--primary);
}
```

